You are calling NoClusterRequiredDummyOperator in the etl_dag.py. This is not meant to be something that the client would ever see, it should only be used within the Quantexa Airflow Cluster object in the library. There is an existing conditional within the Quantexa Airflow Cluster objec that we wrote, which checks if someone needs a cluster and if not calls the Dummy Operator - but the front-end DAG remained consistent for the user, they would just call .create on the Quantexa Airflow Cluster object and the backend handles the rest. 

I think this should be maintained, the DAG shouldn't contain calls to Dummy Operators, this isn't a concept we'd want people to have to get their heads around to use the DAGs, they are only there to handle back-end functionality

Would raise the original exception instead of creating a new one from Exception as you could potentially lose information. The logger logs your custom string anyway so may as well leave the original exception intact IMO (i.e. 
except Exception as e:
...handle exception...
raise
). 
Also the string representation of an exception {e} doesn't always include full detail (e.g. try printing a key error).

